[
  {
    "id": "flow27",
    "type": "tab",
    "label": "MAVLink AI - 27 Offboard Move Sequence",
    "disabled": false,
    "info": "The real guided/offboard workflow: start a setpoint stream, switch the vehicle into a setpoint-accepting mode, steer by refreshing the streamed setpoint, and stop cleanly.\n\nOrdering matters on PX4: OFFBOARD refuses to engage (and drops out) unless a setpoint stream of >= ~2 Hz is ALREADY flowing, so step 1 starts the stream before step 2 switches the mode. ArduPilot GUIDED does not need the pre-stream, but the same sequence works there too - just pick GUIDED in step 2.\n\nSteps: 1) start the built-in stream holding zero velocity (the move node resends it at 5 Hz until stopped), 2) set the mode with Await ack so the debug shows the vehicle accepted it, 3) send a discrete position target (one-shot: up 5 m, 10 m North), 4) steer by refreshing the SAME streaming node - the inject overrides velocity via msg.payload and the stream picks it up on its next tick, 5) stop the stream with msg.payload.stream=false (the node also tears the stream down on redeploy/close).\n\nSending: the moves and the mode command send directly through the shared UDP connection (streaming requires a Connection - there is nowhere to stream a build-only message). Point it at your SITL or vehicle; the SITL example's ./test flows use the same 0.0.0.0:14550 bind. Debug nodes show the mode ack and any structured mavlink/error.\n\nAltitude/climb are entered up-positive; the move node maps them to NED's negative z/vz for you. If the profile firmware is ArduPilot or PX4 the node also raises advisory warnings for mask/frame combinations that firmware is known not to honor (force setpoints, PX4 OFFSET frames, ...)."
  },
